# Membly Project Structure

## Entry Point
The application starts at [main.dart](mdc:lib/main.dart) which initializes the app theme and routing.

## Core Layer (`lib/core/`)
Foundation classes that are used throughout the app:

- [app_constants.dart](mdc:lib/core/constants/app_constants.dart) - Game configuration, color definitions, icon lists
- [app_theme.dart](mdc:lib/core/themes/app_theme.dart) - ThemeData configuration with cyberpunk color scheme
- [haptic_utils.dart](mdc:lib/core/utils/haptic_utils.dart) - Vibration feedback utilities
- [format_utils.dart](mdc:lib/core/utils/format_utils.dart) - Time and score formatting

## Data Layer (`lib/data/`)
Data models and local storage:

- [level_model.dart](mdc:lib/data/models/level_model.dart) - Level configuration model
- [card_model.dart](mdc:lib/data/models/card_model.dart) - Card state model
- [game_state_model.dart](mdc:lib/data/models/game_state_model.dart) - Complete game state
- [local_storage.dart](mdc:lib/data/local/local_storage.dart) - SharedPreferences wrapper

## Presentation Layer (`lib/presentation/`)
UI components organized by type:

### Screens
- [home_screen.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/screens/home_screen.dart) - Main menu
- [game_screen.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/screens/game_screen.dart) - Game play area
- Result and pause overlays are shown as modals within game_screen

### Widgets
- [card_widget.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/widgets/card_widget.dart) - Flippable card component
- [timer_bar.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/widgets/timer_bar.dart) - Animated progress bar
- [hud_widget.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/widgets/hud_widget.dart) - Game stats display
- [particle_background.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/widgets/particle_background.dart) - Animated background
- [combo_indicator.dart](mdc:lib/presentation/widgets/combo_indicator.dart) - Floating combo text

## File Naming Convention
- Use snake_case for file names
- Suffix widgets with `_widget.dart`
- Suffix screens with `_screen.dart`
- Suffix models with `_model.dart`
- Suffix utils with `_utils.dart`

## Import Order
1. Dart/Flutter SDK imports
2. Package imports
3. Local imports (relative paths)
4. Separate groups with blank line
